'''''Shankar Guru''''' ({{lang-kn|ಶಂಕರ್ ಗುರು}}) is a [[Kannada films of 1978|1978]] Indian [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada]] film directed by [[V. Somashekhar]] starring [[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]], [[Kanchana (actress)|Kanchana]], [[Jaimala (actress)|Jaimala]] in lead roles. The supporting cast features [[Padmapriya (actress)|Padmapriya]], [[Balakrishna (Kannada actor)|Balakrishna]], [[Vajramuni]], [[Thoogudeepa Srinivas]] and [[Uma Shivakumar]]. Rajkumar appeared in a triple role in the film — as a father and his two sons separated in childhood.

The film is considered one of the best Kannada films of the 1970s and is seen as a milestone in the career of Rajkumar.<ref>{{cite web|title=The best of Dr Rajkumar|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/apr/17raj.htm|publisher=''[[Rediff.com]]''|date=17 April 2006|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref> It was remade in [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] as ''[[Thirisoolam]]'' (1979), in Telugu as ''Kumara Raja''(1978) and in [[Bollywood|Hindi]] as ''[[Mahaan]]'' (1983) in which, Rajkumar's characters were played by [[Sivaji Ganesan]], [[Krishna (Telugu actor)|Krishna]] and [[Amitabh Bachchan]] respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title= Top ten Kannada films to have been remade |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/Top-ten-Kannada-films-to-have-been-remade/photostory/27975825.cms |newspaper= The Times of India |accessdate= 1 May 2014}}</ref><ref>https://bollyspice.com/framing-movies-take-twenty-four-mahaan-1983/</ref>The movie was declared an ''Industry hit'' at the box office.

==Plot==

Rajashekhar's ([[Rajkumar (actor)|Rajkumar]]) business partners arrive at his house on his birthday and wedding anniversary with a bouquet of flowers to his pregnant wife Sumati and arrange a meeting that evening. They announce their decision to smuggle [[Murti|idol]]s of deities abroad to which Rajashekhar opposes causing a rift between them killing one of them in the process. Pursued by police, he escapes with his wife Sumathi, only to be stranded at the railway station with his wife going separating from him. Sumati, delivers a baby boy, takes up painting and gets on with life.

Years roll by, Rajashekhar is living in Srinagar, Kashmir as a wealthy estate owner named as Jairaj. 
Sumati's son Shankar finds out about his father and also learns about his twin brother Guru.<br />
Thrilling sequences interspersed with comedy and romance make for a heady climax.

